'''Nikumbha''' (<U+0928><U+093F><U+0915><U+0941><U+092E><U+094D><U+200D><U+092D>) is a [[Demon#In Hinduism|demon]] in [[Hinduism|Hindu]] [[Hindu mythology|mythology]]<ref name="experiencefestival">{{cite web |url= http://www.experiencefestival.com/a/Nikumbha/id/141810 |title= Nikumbha|accessdate=2007-01-22 |work= Sanskrit Hinduism Dictionary III}}</ref> and is the son of [[Kumbha (demon)|Kumbha]].<ref name="sacred-texts">{{cite web |url= http://www.sacred-texts.com/hin/dutt/rama09.htm|title= Ramayana Book IX|accessdate= 2007-01-22|last= C. Dutt|first= Romesh |date= 1899|work= The Ramayana and Mahabharata |publisher= Internet Sacred Text Archive}}</ref> He was instructed by [[Kubera]] to watch over the [[Pisaca]]s,<ref name="purana">{{cite web |url= http://www.koausa.org/Purana/Verses201-300.html |title= Verses 201-300 |accessdate=2007-01-22|work= Nilamata Purana}}</ref> (a type of evil spirit),<ref name="pisaca">{{cite web |url= http://vedabase.net/sb/2/6/43-45/|title= <U+015A>r<U+012B>mad Bh<U+0101>gavatam 2.6.43-45|accessdate=2007-01-22 |format= |work= Bhaktivedanta VedaBase}}</ref> and the [[Nilamata Purana]] refers to him as "the noble and strong lord of the Pisacas."<ref name="purana"/>

